      "acceptanceCriteria": "QOI (NIH, RH index) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint of hemolysis risk and accepted by regulatory precedent.",
      "rationale": "NIH and relative hemolysis index RH are standard FDA-recognized metrics for hemolysis assessment in blood-contacting devices. These QOIs are directly tied to the clinical risk of red blood cell damage and are consistent with FDA guidance on hemolysis testing."
